com.adobe.cq.social.subscriptions.client.api

Class AbstractSubscriptionCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.cq.social.scf.core.BaseSocialComponent
      • com.adobe.cq.social.subscriptions.client.api.AbstractSubscriptionCollection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SocialComponent, SubscriptionCollection

    public class AbstractSubscriptionCollection
extends BaseSocialComponent
implements SubscriptionCollection
    Base class of SCF SubscriptionCollection component. A subscription collection represents a relationships between a user and a resource or another user. The value of the userId and the followedId is obtained in the following order: If the request is a Post request, then the userId and the followedId are obtained from the request parameters. If the request is a Get request, then:

    1. The userId is obtained from the resource Following.PROP_USERID property; If this property does not exist, the userId is obtained from the request's session user id.

    2. The followedId is obtained from the resource Following.PROP_FOLLOWEDID property; If this property does not exist, the userId is obtained from the resource name
